   <title type="text">Logeion is now an app for iOS 7 devices</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[From postings to mailing list be Helma Dik<br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">What was only (?) a website for Greek and Latin diction at <a href="http://logeion.uchicago.edu" target="_blank">logeion.uchicago.edu</a> is now also available as an app for iOS 7 devices:&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/logeion/id727860177?ls=1&amp;mt=8" target="_blank">https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/logeion/id727860177?ls=1&amp;mt=8</a></span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">(searching for Logeion will likely not yet yield results in the App  Store; things will need to propagate to its indices. For now, use the  direct link above)</span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">For those with older systems, Lexiphanes (for Greek) and Lexidium (Latin) are still excellent substitutes.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">What's in Logeion: LSJ, Autenrieth, Lewis &amp; Short, and much  more for the low low price of FREE. Brought to you thanks to the Perseus  Project's (Tufts University) policy to license its materials  generously, and to Josh Day's labors to wrap it in a convenient  package for iOS devices.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">Enjoy!</span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">Helma</span></div><span style="font-size: x-small;">-- <br />Helma Dik </span><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">Department of Classics</span></div><div><span style="font-size: x-small;">University of Chicago</span></div></blockquote>]]></content>
